properties.areaDesc: Coastal waters from Tarpon Springs to Suwannee River FL out 20 NM
properties.headline: Small Craft Advisory issued February 6 at 3:52AM EST until February 7 at 10:00AM EST by NWS Tampa Bay Ruskin FL
properties.description:
* WHAT...For the Gale Warning, south winds 25 to 30 kt with gusts
over 45 kt and seas 9 to 11 feet expected. For the Small Craft
Advisory, west winds 20 to 25 kt with gusts up to 30 kt and seas
7 to 9 feet expected.

* WHERE...Coastal waters from Tarpon Springs to Suwannee River
FL out 20 NM.

* WHEN...For the Gale Warning, from 1 PM Thursday to 1 AM EST
Friday. For the Small Craft Advisory, from 1 AM to 10 AM EST
Friday.

* IMPACTS...Strong winds will cause hazardous seas which could
capsize or damage vessels.
properties.instruction:
Mariners should alter plans to avoid these hazardous conditions.
Remain in port, seek safe harbor, alter course, and/or secure the
vessel for severe conditions.

NWSheadline: GALE WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 1 PM THIS AFTERNOON TO 1 AM EST FRIDAY... ...SMALL CRAFT ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 1 AM TO 10 AM EST FRIDAY
